            <h3>Profile and course description.</h3>
            <strong><h5>History</h5></strong>
            <p>
              The Department of Economics has offered the BA Social Sciences (combined degree) with emphasis in Economics since the 1970’s.
            <br>
              Ghana had independence in 1957 and the government saw the need to train skilled manpower to take over from the Colonial Masters. Consequently, KNUST was upgraded to university status in 1961.
            <br>
              The Department of Economics was established in 1974 to train skilled manpower with knowledge in Intermediate and Advanced Economics models and theories.  
            <br>
              From 2004/2005 academic year the department has offered BA degree in Economics.</p>
            <br>
            <strong><h5>Goals and objectives</h5></strong>
            <p><strong>a)</strong>  To train medium and high level manpower for Ghana and the international community.<br>
            <strong>b)</strong>  To provide service to other departments in KNUST<br>
            The Department of Economics provides service courses to all the colleges in KNUST. The Department teaches both graduate (e.g. MSc. Agriculture Economics, MSc. Environmental Management) and undergraduate courses in other departments.<br>
            <strong>c)</strong>  Multi-disciplinary programmes-the department of economics is crucial for multi-disciplinary programmes for example in the area of medical sciences, we teach health economics, in the engineering there is energy economics and in the sciences there is environmental economics<br>
            <strong>d)</strong>  Senior members of the department serve on committees set up by the University <br>
            <strong>e)</strong>  Senior members provide service to Ghana:<br>
            <il>•   Senior members serve as external examiners and moderators to other sister institutions</il><br> 
            <il>•   examiners to international examining boards like the WAEC</il><br>
            <il>•   members of boards of national institutions </il><br>
            <il>•   To provide consultancy services to public and private institutions in Ghana.</il><br> 
            <il>•   The Department significantly generate funds internally through its admission of both local and international students.</il></p>
